An alert is triggered when log data matches a rule, such as:

A specific error code appears

Too many errors in a time window

A critical service stops

Security-related events (failed logins, privilege changes)

3. Common alert conditions

Threshold-based:
“More than 5 errors in 1 minute”

Pattern-based:
“Log message contains ‘OutOfMemoryError’”

Anomaly-based:
“Error rate is higher than normal”

Absence-based:
“No heartbeat log for 10 minutes”

4. Alert delivery
Alerts are usually sent via:

Email

Slack / Teams

PagerDuty / Opsgenie

SMS / push notifications

Dashboards

5. Popular tools
Depending on your stack:

ELK / OpenSearch (Elasticsearch + alerting rules)

Splunk (saved searches + alerts)

Prometheus + Alertmanager (for metrics derived from logs)

AWS CloudWatch Alarms

Azure Monitor Alerts

Datadog / New Relic
